# *PiCam*

**PiCam** A Python Library that allows a Public Payphone to take and post pictures to Twitter.
This project is an extension of Public Payphone [http://leimertphonecompany.net]

## Installation

Pi-Phone Cam requires the following libraries:
Pygame:  pip install pygame
Tweepy:  pip install tweepy
Rpi.GPIO pip install rpi.gpio
Create a Twitter Account and Get credentials at: https://dev.twitter.com/

## User Stories

* [x] GPIO are mapped to Phone Dialpad
* [x] Using Dialpad user can take pictures and upload them to Twitter

## Open Source Libraries Used
- [https://pypi.python.org/pypi/RPi.GPIO] (RPi.GPIO) - Python GPIO Library
- [http://www.tweepy.org/] (Tweepy) - A Python Twitter API Library
- [http://www.pygame.org/hifi.html] (Pygame) - A Python Gaming library, in this case used to Load soundfiles.
Any sound python library would do.

A better implementation using Alsa: http://blog.scphillips.com/posts/2013/01/sound-configuration-on-raspberry-pi-with-alsa/
